The last vvill and testament of the Earl of Pembroke.
4 p.
s.n., [London? : 1650]
A satire on the Earl of Pembroke. A different work from "The first part of the last wil & testament of Philip Earle of Pembrooke and Montgomery, Lord of Saint Quintin, &c. now Knight of Berk-shire" and "The last will and testament of Philip Herbert, burgesse for Bark-shire, vulgarly called Earl of Pembroke and Montgomery". Caption title. Wing suggests 1679 as publication date; dated on internal evidence. Reproduction of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
